This appeal was filed by the State of Andhra Pradesh against the conviction and sentence of two accused persons, Rayavarapu Punnayya (Respondent 1) and his wife, M. Ramalakshmi (Respondent 2), under Section 302 read with Section 34, Penal Code, for murder.

The facts of the case are as follows: The husband and wife were belonging to different communities and had been at odds with each other since long. Bitter communal litigation was going on between them. One day, when the two parties were passing through a village called Nekarikal, Punnayya got down from his vehicle and deliberately trailed Ramalakshmi, beating her mercilessly with sticks in a brutal manner. He smashed at least seven bones, mostly major bones, and dislocated two more. Despite his protests, he continued the beating till she became unconscious.

The prosecution alleged that the accused duo beat up the deceased on account of their communal differences and that the injuries caused were sufficient to cause death even if they were not intended to be fatal.

After trial, the accused duo was convicted under Section 302 read with Section 34, Penal Code. However, on appeal, the High Court reduced the conviction to Section 304, Part II, Penal Code.

The accused duo appealed against this order of the High Court before us.

We have heard the learned counsel for both sides and are of the opinion that the judgment of the High Court is wrong and hence, we allow this appeal and restore the order of the trial Court convicting the accused persons under Section 302 read with Section 34, Penal Code. The accused persons, if not already in jail, shall be arrested and committed to prison to serve out the sentence inflicted on them.

The judgment of the High Court is set aside, and the conviction of Respondent 2 remains intact.
